apCctExtMib.description: The MIB module used to describe the ArrowPoint Communications Circuit information

apCctTable.name: apCctTable
apCctTable.description: A list of information for the specified circuit.

apCctEntry.name: apCctEntry
apCctEntry.description: A group of information to uniquely identify a circuit.

apCctIfIndex.name: apCctIfIndex
apCctIfIndex.description: The unique if Index assigned to this circuit.

apCctName.name: apCctName
apCctName.description: The name of the circuit auto-generated by Circuit manager.

apCctDescription.name: apCctDescription
apCctDescription.description: The user defined description string associated with the circuit

apCctIfType.name: apCctIfType
apCctIfType.description: The interface type of this circuit.

apCctState.name: apCctState
apCctState.description: The state of the circuit. Circuit is active if it has one or more active ports associated with it.

apCctLinkCount.name: apCctLinkCount
apCctLinkCount.description: The number of logical links configured on this circuit.

apCctAclIndex.name: apCctAclIndex
apCctAclIndex.description: The ACL which is currently in use on the circuit.

apCctL2Redundancy.name: apCctL2Redundancy
apCctL2Redundancy.description: If enabled, this switch is configured to provide redundancy for this circuit with another switch. Only the active switch will actually receive and forward traffic; the second will be a hot backup.

apCctIrdpUseLimitedBcast.name: apCctIrdpUseLimitedBcast
apCctIrdpUseLimitedBcast.description: Enable/disable the use of the limited broadcast address 255.255.255.255 for the transmission of router discovery packets. Default is false (use multicast address 224.0.0.1). This parameter has no meaning if the link does not support multicast (255.255.255.255 will be used).

apCctIrdpMaxInterval.name: apCctIrdpMaxInterval
apCctIrdpMaxInterval.description: Maximum interval between advertisements (seconds). Default is 600 seconds.

apCctIrdpMinInterval.name: apCctIrdpMinInterval
apCctIrdpMinInterval.description: Minimum interval between advertisements (seconds). Default (0) means use 0.75 times max. If non-zero, this value must be less than apCctIrdpMax.

apCctIrdpLifetime.name: apCctIrdpLifetime
apCctIrdpLifetime.description: Value placed in the lifetime field of a router advertisement. Default (0) means use 3 times the max. If non-zero, this value must be greater than apCctIrdpMax.
